# BigBad Frontend Web Standards

## Architecture

- Prefer **feature-oriented** structure; keep domain logic separate from UI where feasible.
- Separate concerns: **UI rendering**, **state/data**, **side effects** (network/storage/analytics).
- Avoid “god components”; extract when state/logic grows.

## Responsive + UX

- Mobile-first; scale up via breakpoints.
- Avoid hover-only interactions; provide tap equivalents.
- Accessible controls and comfortable touch targets.

## Error handling

- User-friendly messages; log technical detail **safely** (no secrets/PII).
- Handle offline/partial failure states when relevant.

